SIMPLE: extravagant
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extravagant
<hw>Ex*trav"a*gant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>extravagant</ets>, fr. L. <ets>extra</ets> on the outside +
<ets>vagans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>vagari</ets> to
wander, from <ets>vagus</ets> wandering, vague. See
<er>Vague</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wandering beyond one's bounds;
roving; hence, foreign.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>extravagant</qex> and erring spirit hies⟦br⟧
To his confine.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exceeding due bounds; wild; excessive; unrestrained;
<as>as, <ex>extravagant</ex> acts, wishes, praise, abuse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There appears something nobly wild and <qex>extravagant</qex> in
great natural geniuses.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Profuse in expenditure; prodigal; wasteful; <as>as,
an <ex>extravagant</ex> man</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Extravagant</xex>
expense.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bancroft.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extravagant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Extravagant
<hw>Ex*trav"a*gant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who is
confined to no general rule.</def> <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>Certain
constitutions or decretal epistles, not at first included with others,
but subsequently made a part of the canon law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extravagantly</ent>⟦br⟧
